<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,310,1758,1784]" box="[189,310,1758,1784]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1758,1784]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1758,1784]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1398,1807,1872]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A large species with all coxae black and fore coxa bearing long white bristles. All femora strongly thickened, hind femur strongest. Hind tibia with a long, blunt flattened apical spur.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,324,1914,1940]" box="[189,324,1914,1940]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1914,1940]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1914,1940]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1398,1963,2027]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The specific name is from the Greek ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[660,757,1963,1989]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Thinophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plektron">
<emphasis box="[660,757,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">plektron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ (‘thing to strike with’: cock’s spur, pick for a lyre) alluding to the apical spur on the hind tibia. It is used as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
